			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Are you looking to put your engineering skills to use building beautiful apps for the iOS platform? Does the idea of working on just one product day in, day-out bore you? Thumb Labs is a boutique mobile agency making a name for itself in the mobile world, building top class iPhone and iPad applications for everyone from early-stage startups to Fortune 500s. Come join an intimate team of designers and developers that are pushing the boundaries of the most exciting technology platform of the last 10 years. The company is driven primarily by client work, so you&#39;ll have an opportunity to work on a wide range of products, but also maintains a keen interest in leveraging our skills to add to our own growing library of consumer applications.</p>
<p>
	With an office located in the Soho district of Manhattan, in the heart of the NYC startup world, employees at Thumb Labs are encouraged to contribute to the larger tech community. You&#39;ll be given all the tools you need to excel and advance in your career.&nbsp;We are looking to foster a casual, but fast-paced startup culture and with your help, hope to build an organization where ideas are valued more than job titles.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities include utilizing Objective C and iOS Frameworks in the development of iPhone and iPad applications. integration with web-based APIs and back-end technologies, and contributing to overall product architecture and development.</p>
<p>
	Of course, while having these skills is important, we are particularly interested in finding a candidate with the right mindset, and a great personality fit. The ideal applicant is a self-starter that is ready to own projects in full, and has an interest and enthusiasm for dabbling with the full technology stack.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>
